=== THE ROYAL PARK SEPT ===

*** ADAPTED TEMPLATE NOTE ***
This entry is a coterie-EQUIVALENT, not a Kindred-style 
coterie. Glass Walker (and broader Garou) social structure 
differs from Kindred coterie structure in three significant 
ways:

(1) SEPT HIERARCHY IS FORMAL. Septs have ranked positions 
(Septleader, Wyrd Warder, Master of the Rite, etc.) that 
exist independent of personal relationships. The Camarilla 
Court has formal positions too, but Camarilla coteries 
typically operate INFORMALLY beneath that formal structure. 
A sept's operational unit IS its formal hierarchy.

(2) PACK BONDS ARE SPIRIT-MEDIATED. Garou packs are bonded 
through totem spirits — the binding is genuinely supernatural, 
not just political. This produces a different texture than 
Kindred coterie binding (which is political-emotional but 
not metaphysically anchored).

(3) KINFOLK ARE FULL MEMBERS. Glass Walker septs include 
mortal kinfolk as full operational members, not as auxiliary 
mortal-network. The kinfolk's mortal status is structural 
rather than peripheral.

The entry below uses the coterie template's POLITICAL-UTILITY 
fields (binding, purpose, internal dynamics, external 
relationships, chronicle pacing) but reorganises them around 
Garou-appropriate structure.
